The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, April 5: Mahindra amp; Mahindra Ltd today said it would raise $200 million through the issue of foreign currency convertible bonds in the international markets. The committee of directors at its meeting held today considered all relevant factors and approved the launch of FCCBs convertible into fully paid equity shares of Rs 10 each, the company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange. The share price of the company closed at Rs 654.05.

 Mumbai, April 5: EDS? open offer for a 52 per cent controlling stake in MphasiS BFL will open on May 22 and close on June 12. The offer price is Rs 204.50 a share, aggregating to Rs 1,697 crore ($380 million). The offer for acquiring 83 million fully paid-up equity shares of face value of Rs 10 each of MphasiS represents 51.72 per cent of the total voting equity share capital of the company. 

 Mumbai, April 5: Major markets, including the Bombay Stock Exchange and the National Stock Exchange, will remain closed tomorrow on account of Ram Navami. The forex and money markets will also remain closed.

 Mumbai, April 5: Karnataka High Court has approved the merger of the Wipro BPO and two overseas companies with Wipro Ltd, the software giant said today. The court okayed the merger of Bermuda-based Spectramind Ltd, Mauritius-located Spectramind Ltd and Wipro BPO Solutions Ltd with the company.

 Calcutta, April 5: Alloy Steels Plant, a SAIL subsidiary, expects to post a turnover exceeding Rs 650 crore in 2005-06, up 15 per cent from the previous year. 

 New Delhi, April 5: Mercer plans to invest $50 million over the next three years in the upcoming global operations centre in Noida, which would be managed by Patni Computers. 

 Mumbai, April 5: The Asset Reconstruction Company India Ltd (Arcil) has recovered and distributed to investors Rs 870 crore from 173 cases of non-performing assets acquired by it.




